17/08/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Two former members of the Republika Srpska (RS) Army -- Miladin Trivic and Slobodan Bajic -- were sentenced Friday (August 14th) to 15 and eight years in prison respectively for war crimes. Their victims in 1993 were Bosniak civilians in Banja Luka. A third former RS army member -- Sinisa Milojevic -- was indicted for the same crimes but is currently at large. (B92 - 16/08/09; RTS, Tanjug - 15/08/09; RTRS, Srna, Fena - 14/08/09)
